cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper focuses on developing machine vision systems for automated classification of natural food products using artificial neural networks. This falls under the domain of computer vision and pattern recognition. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper extensively uses artificial neural networks as classifiers for the machine vision systems. This falls under the domain of machine learning. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper uses artificial neural networks, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence, to develop the machine vision systems. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper involves the use of image processing techniques to extract spectral patterns from the images of natural food products. This can be considered as a form of information retrieval. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper uses artificial neural networks extensively, which falls under the domain of neural and evolutionary computing.
